Grumman Corp said it was awardeda 28 mln dlr contract by McDonnell Douglas Corp &lt;MD> to developflight control surfaces for the United States Air Force's newC-17 transport aircraft.    Grumman said it will design, develop and build the ailerons, rudders and elevators for the transport.    The company said the production phase of the contract has apotential value of about 300 mln dlrs. Reuter&#3;